<div class="container">
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Comic Sans MS'">Black Knapweed</h2>
    <h3>Centaurea nigra L.</h3>
</div>


<div class="container marketing" style="margin-top: -4%;">

    <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->
    <hr class="featurette-divider">

    <!-- ***This is the home section, could provides general introduction about Alligator Weed, using the css file
    from Content/template_page, assigned with ID=home to corresponding the function of navigator.*** -->
    <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <h2 class="featurette-heading">About Black knapweed. <span class="text-muted">It'll blow your mind.</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">
                Centaurea refers to the medicine man Chiron, because of the medicinal properties of some plants in this genus.
                Nigra is Latin for black and refers to the dark coloured flower bracts.
                Black Knapweed - Knap is from knop meaning knob or bud and refers to the conspicuous buds of these plants. Black refers to the dark bracts surrounding the flower head. An erect, red-purple flowered, perennial thistle with dark flower head bracts and many stems.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="~/css/images/plants/black-knapweed-1.jpg"  alt="Generic placeholder image">
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="featurette-divider">

    <!-- ***This is the identify section, could provides the identifying methods about Alligator Weed, using the css file
    from Content/template_page, assigned with ID=identify to corresponding the function of navigator.*** -->
    <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="~/css/images/plants/BlackKnapweed_Photo2.jpg" alt="Generic placeholder image">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7" style="margin-top: -5%;">
            <h2 class="featurette-heading">Black knapweed is a State prohibited weed: <span class="text-muted">See for yourself.</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">
                State prohibited weeds are the highest category of declared noxious weeds in Victoria.
                By definition they are either not yet in Victoria, or are here in small numbers, where their eradication is still possible.
                Black knapweed Seed is distributed by attachment to passing animals. The pappus is too small to allow effective dispersal by wind.
                Root fragments readily shoot when damaged and cultivation often spreads the infestation within a field.
                Perennial roots are not affected by fire.

            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="featurette-divider">

    <!-- ***This is the control section, could provides suggestion about how to control Alligator Weed,
    or the contact details about related organization to control them, this also using the css file
    from Content/template_page, assigned with ID=control to corresponding the function of navigator.*** -->
    <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <h2 class="featurette-heading">How can I identify it? <span class="text-muted">Checkmate.</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">
                In Black Knapweed Bracts surrounding flower head are dark, not spiny, and have long comb like teeth hiding the base of the bract.
                They Have Purple flowers.
                Ridged stems turn purple when mature

            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-5">
            <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="~/css/images/plants/black-knapweed-ide.jpg" alt="Generic placeholder image">
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="featurette-divider">

    <!-- ***This is the identify section, could provides the identifying methods about Alligator Weed, using the css file
    from Content/template_page, assigned with ID=identify to corresponding the function of navigator.*** -->
